15/03/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The constituent session of the BiH Parliament's House of Peoples (HoP) wrapped up on Wednesday (March 14th), with the election of chamber leaders. 
Ilija Filipovic of the Croatian Democratic Union was elected as HoP Speaker, while Sulejman Tihic of the Bosniak Party of Democratic Action and Mladen Ivanic of the Serb Party of Democratic Progress were made deputy speakers. 
Leadership of the HoP will be rotated among the three every eight months.
In other news Wednesday, Republika Srpska (RS) new government's marked its first 100 days in office with a meeting of cabinet ministers and RS President Milan Jelic in Banja Luka. 
RS Prime Minister Milorad Dodik expressed the entity government's willingness to work with the Federation of BiH's administration and the state-level Council of Ministers to determine priority issues. 
(RTRS, Srna, PBS BiH, Pincom.info, Fena - 14/03/07)
